
'''IPLeft is a social group for information commons in South Korea.''' 

URL = http://www.ipleft.or.kr


=Description=


"It was founded in 1999. IPLeft has concerned about the
social and digital divide and criticized the strengthening of
intellectual property rights(IPRs) [or limited intellectual
monopolies] regime and has researched alternative policies
against existing IPR. IPLeft believes that IPR should not
deter the free and balanced flow of ideas and innovations and
the cultural basis of information commons should be socially
wide-spread for the real innovation and creation."
(description from PatchA)


